[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish Open: Mark Allen fights back to defeat Christopher Keogan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Northern Ireland's Mark Allen came from 3-0 down to clinch a 4-3 comeback victory over Christopher Keogan in the first round the Scottish Open.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Doncaster player Keogan, who is 123rd in the world rankings, was on course for an upset when he took the opening three frames in Glasgow.
Allen won all four remaining frames to set up a second-round contest against Fang Xiongman.
Belfast's Joe Swail also progressed after beating Lee Walker 4-1.
Swail will take on Kritsanut Lertsattayathorn or Stuart Carrington in the second round at the Emirates Arena.
